The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Gillette Indias net profit declined to Rs 5.92 crore for the quarter ended June 30 from Rs 17.57 crore for the corresponding quarter in 2005-06. Total income increased to Rs 147.56 crore, up 26.47 per cent from Rs 116.67 crore a year ago, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. 

 Graphite Indias net profit in the quarter ended June 30 was Rs 115.31 crore compared with Rs 7.34 crore a year ago. Profit before tax and extraordinary income was Rs 27.84 crore against Rs 10.04 crore a year ago. 

 Megasoft Ltds profit after tax was Rs 8.07 crore in the quarter ended June 30 against Rs 4.63 crore in the same period last year. Revenues rose 42 per cent to Rs 37.72 crore from Rs 26.61 crore a year ago. 

 Shree Cements net profit for the quarter ended June 2006 was Rs 90.39 crore against Rs 26 crore a year ago. Net sales was Rs 309.39 crore compared with Rs 142.52 crore. Operating profit rose to Rs 140.50 crore from Rs 44.73 crore in the previous year.

 HMT Ltd suffered a net loss of Rs 12.95 crore for the quarter ended June 30 compared with a net loss of Rs 1.56 crore a year ago. Total income was down 62.06 per cent at Rs 22.54 crore against Rs 59.42 crore.

 Su-Raj Diamonds amp; Jewellerys net profit in the first quarter of the current fiscal jumped 22.47 per cent to Rs 9.21 crore, up from Rs 7.52 crore in the same period last year. Sales turnover was up 15.67 per cent to Rs 310 crore from Rs 268 crore. 

 Blue Star Ltds net profit in the quarter ended June 30 was Rs 7.3 crore. Total income was Rs 312.81 crore and earnings per share increased to Rs 4.06 from Rs 2.80.

 Kewal Kiran Clothing Ltds profit after tax was Rs 4.57 crore in the quarter ended June 30. Revenues were at Rs 29.31 crore. 

 KPIT Cummins Infosystems net profit for the quarter ended June 30 was Rs 10.3 crore. The companys revenues were Rs 102.2 crore.

 Zicom Electronic Security Systems net profit in the quarter ended June 30 was Rs 2.07 crore. Its total income stood at Rs 31.1 crore in the quarter. 

 Bongaigaon Refinery and Petrochemicals Ltd (BRPL) has posted an 18.80 per cent rise in net profit to Rs 81.74 crore for the quarter ended June 30 from Rs 68.80 crore in the corresponding quarter a year ago.

